  "text": "Motor skill handedness assessment To determine a more accurate measure of hand skill and motor co-ordination, and to serve as an additional confirmation of motor difficulties in the DCD group, the participants carried out an electronic version of the peg-moving task described by [CITATION_1] . The dimensions of the board and peg movement procedure were identical; however, to improve timing accuracy, the board was constructed to allow detection of peg lifting and placing via an electrical circuit in the board. This was connected to the PC's parallel port, where a Visual Basic programme continuously monitored and recorded the times at which pegs were removed from or inserted into the holes.",
